reviewText: I enjoy vintage books and movies so I enjoyed reading this book. The plot was unusual.
Loved the suspense in the story. Couldn't put it down.
It was an okay read. Not the best I've had.
I absolutely loved this fantasy book. The characters were amazing.
The romantic elements felt a bit forced to me.
The suspense was gripping. Couldn't predict the ending at all.
An enthralling tale set in a dystopian future. A masterpiece!
The historical accuracies in the book were commendable. Enjoyed the deep dive into the past.
The mystery element was well-executed. Kept me guessing till the end.
It was okay. The high school drama felt too exaggerated.
A delightful read! The author's writing style is unique and engaging.
The adventure sequences were breathtaking! Felt like I was on the journey with the characters.
A deep dive into the reality of the subject. Enlightening and educational.
